<theme id="thm217">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Triplet tied to next note</title>
<tocimage>img217.png</tocimage>

<para>In this lesson two new rhythmic patterns are introduced. They are the result of
tying a triplet to the next note:</para>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4 noVisible)
        (n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t- l)(n * q)
        (n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t- l)(n * e g+)(n * e g-)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>

<part>
<title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>
<para>Note the difference between the first and the second measure, and between the third and
the fourth ones. Note how
measures 2 and 4 are similar to measures 1 and 3 but tying the triplets.</para>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4)
           (n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t-)(n * q)
        (n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t- l)(n * q)
        (n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t-)(n * e g+)(n * e g-)
        (n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e l g- t-)(n * e g+)(n * e g-)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>
</part>

<part>
<title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm217_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear and practise the
introduced rhythmic patterns.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm217_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>

</part>

</theme>

